27 Customisation
****************

Ebib can be customised through Emacs' standard customisation interface.
The relevant customisation group is (obviously) called `ebib', which
has four subgroups: `ebib-faces', `ebib-filters', and `ebib-keywords',
whose functions should be obvious, and `ebib-windows', where options
for Ebib's window management can be set. All options are documented in
the customisation buffers. You can go to Ebib's customisation buffer
with `M-x customize-group RET ebib RET', or by using the menu «Ebib |
Options | Customize Ebib».

   Another way to customise Ebib is to use the initialisation file
`~/.emacs.d/ebibrc'. (Actually, the location and name of this file can
be customised as well.) This file contains normal Lisp code and is the
best way to customise key bindings (as discussed in the next section),
but it can in fact be used to run any Lisp code.

